{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":"Bryan Tinsley","await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"Done","closed_at":"2026-03-07T04:24:42Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"9de5b48e2bc0c726affe0a94704ea10491ef4ef1100d2252ecef0124aeaedf2d","created_at":"2026-03-07T04:16:25Z","created_by":"Bryan Tinsley","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Goal: Three display modes for tool calls in chat view.\n\nMode 1 - Minimal: Only show tools that change state (Edit, Write, Bash with side effects). Hide read-only tools (Read, Glob, Grep, WebFetch, WebSearch). Bash is ambiguous - inspect command for read-only patterns (ls, cat, grep, git status) vs mutation (git commit, npm install, rm). When in doubt, show it.\n\nMode 2 - Normal (DEFAULT): All tool calls visible but collapsed (tool name + file/command summary in one line). Click to expand.\n\nMode 3 - Full: Everything fully expanded. Current behavior, for debugging.\n\nUI: Three-way toggle or dropdown in chat settings. Persisted per-workspace in localStorage. Mode change applies retroactively (re-renders existing messages).\n\nSafety: Do NOT change tool event persistence - rendering only. Default to Normal.","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"klaudii-ab3","is_template":0,"issue_type":"feature","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"bryan@tinsley.me","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"Tool call display modes: Minimal, Normal, Full","updated_at":"2026-03-07T04:24:42Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
